The paper proposes a novel approach for deep learning based deformable image registration, which involves the use of convolutional layers and a learnable bicubic Catmull-Rom spline resampler. This approach is evaluated on public datasets of 4D CT lung and brain images. Given the focus on image processing and machine learning techniques, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The use of deep learning also suggests that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of optimization techniques, which could place it in the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. Finally, the use of convolutional layers and resampling techniques suggests that the paper could also be relevant to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
